events.1537: Fort constructed on the riverbank of Asunción, later becoming the colony's capital
events.1541: Garrison of Buenos Aires abandons the town and resettles in Asunción
events.1811: Military and political uprising in Asunción against governor Velasco, beginning of Paraguay's independence
events.1812: National Congress meets for the first time in Asunción
events.1841: Carlos Antonio López assumes power, establishing his dictatorship in Asunción
events.1868: Allied armies occupy Asunción, ending the Paraguayan War
events.1869: Paraguayan army defeated at the Battle of Acosta Ñu, leading to the collapse of the army and occupation of Asunción
events.1870: Provisional government collapses in Asunción, Cirilo Antonio Rivarola elected president
events.1882: Bernardino Caballero controversially elected president in Asunción
events.2008: Fernando Lugo elected president, ending the 66-year rule of the Colorado Party in Asunción
events.2012: Impeachment of Fernando Lugo, Federico Franco takes over the presidency in Asunción
